transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi. My name is Thurman Yelvington.

Speaker 1: I got a charge on my card for Viagra, and I did not receive any.

Speaker 2: I did not order any.

Speaker 1: I want to put a check on my account.

Speaker 2: Do not send me anything unless I call.

Speaker 1: And I'd like to have my $63 back.

Speaker 2: I called yesterday.

Speaker 1: So if you want us to set it up so you can order as needed, we can do that.

Speaker 2: It looks like that's already how you are set up from yesterday.

Speaker 1: So what is it that you need?

Speaker 2: I want to stop everything.

Speaker 1: So what did you call yesterday for?

Speaker 2: To tell them that.

Speaker 1: They told me I had to call back today because I have not received anything from y'all.

Speaker 2: Well, I seen that you were put on hold so you can order as needed.

Speaker 1: That's what you did yesterday.

Speaker 2: I did not order.

Speaker 1: Listen, man.

Speaker 2: I did not order nothing.

Speaker 1: I did not receive nothing.

Speaker 2: I didn't say you ordered anything.

Speaker 1: Can you just listen?

Speaker 2: If you'd listen, then you would understand and we can get through this.

Speaker 1: I said you called in yesterday and you were put on hold to order as needed going for the future.

Speaker 2: You did not cancel yesterday.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Fine.

Speaker 1: I did not receive anything.

Speaker 2: Just saying I did receive it.

Speaker 1: I did not receive anything.

Speaker 2: Let's check the tracking.

Speaker 1: Let's check the tracking.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: It does look like that.

Speaker 2: It says it was delivered yesterday at 5 p.m.

Speaker 1: I have not received anything and I did not order anything.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: You ordering and you receiving something is two completely different things.

Speaker 2: If you say you didn't order it, that's fine, but that wouldn't change something getting delivered to your address or not.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, I haven't received anything in my address.

Speaker 1: The post office did give us confirmation it was delivered at your mailbox at 1:35 p.m. yesterday.

Speaker 2: Then somebody stole it because I didn't receive it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, you're going to have to call the post office and see what's going on with that, sir, because it was delivered to you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So I've got to eat my $63 in?

Speaker 1: No, sir.

Speaker 2: No, sir.

Speaker 1: I mean, you can send it back and we can give you a full refund.

Speaker 2: If I don't have something, how am I going to send it back?

Speaker 1: It should be there, sir.

Speaker 2: Maybe look in the bushes or something.

Speaker 1: I don't know.

Speaker 2: I'm not going to argue with you about this.

Speaker 1: Y'all keep the $63.

Speaker 2: Don't send me nothing else no more.

Speaker 1: It's not an argument, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm simply just telling you what the post office gave us.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And I'm telling you it ain't here and it's not here.

Speaker 1: That's what I'm telling you.

Speaker 2: Well, it should be, sir, because the post office did confirm.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Talking to y'all ain't doing no good.

Speaker 1: Just don't send nothing out there.
